---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<Layout title="Taxonomy" description="The V/Q spatial scaling law, bifurcation axis, and HeadGenome atlas.">
<div class="page-top">
  <p class="eyebrow">01 — Taxonomy</p>
  <h1>One probe.<br/>Four classes.<br/>Every architecture.</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    Using only the ratio of value-norm to query-norm (V/Q) and an entropy-collapse
    probe on 200 prompts, we recover a four-class taxonomy with p ≈ 10⁻¹²⁷ —
    across GPT-2, Qwen-0.5B, Qwen-1.5B, and Llama-3.2-1B.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h2 class="reveal">The V/Q Spatial Scaling Law</h2>
  <p class="reveal">
    The functional role of an attention head is strictly governed by its ‖W_V‖/‖W_Q‖ norm ratio,
    dictating a mathematically inevitable spatial progression through network depth.
    Early-layer heads are query-dominated → local attention.
    Late-layer heads are value-dominated → global retrieval.
    This law holds across all four architectures with p ≈ 1.92 × 10⁻¹²⁷.
  </p>
  <figure class="figure reveal">
    <img src={`${base}/figures/fig1_vq_scaling.png`} alt="V/Q scaling law" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption>The V/Q ratio vs. relative depth for all 1,568 heads. The monotonic rise is universal across MHA (GPT-2) and GQA (Qwen, Llama) architectures.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <hr/>

  <h2 class="reveal">The Bifurcation Axis</h2>
  <p class="reveal">
    At ~40–60% network depth, the developmental manifold bifurcates. Most heads continue
    as Local precursors. A minority split into Retrieval or Induction specialisations.
    The bifurcation axis is orthogonal to the V/Q scaling law and defines the second
    axis of variation in the taxonomy.
  </p>
  <figure class="figure reveal">
    <img src={`${base}/figures/fig2_bifurcation.png`} alt="Bifurcation axis" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption>Retrieval and Induction heads peel away from the Local trajectory at a characteristic depth, driven by entropy-collapse on different query targets.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <hr/>

  <h2 class="reveal">The HeadGenome Atlas</h2>
  <p class="reveal">
    Projecting all 1,568 heads onto the (V/Q, entropy) plane produces a 2D map in which
    the four classes occupy non-overlapping, reproducible regions across every model tested.
  </p>
  <figure class="figure reveal">
    <img src={`${base}/figures/atlas.png`} alt="HeadGenome atlas" loading="lazy" />
    <figcaption>Each dot is one attention head, coloured by functional class. The four clusters are geometrically separated and architecture-invariant.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <hr/>

  <h2 class="reveal">Head counts by architecture</h2>
  <div class="reveal">
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Model</th><th>Attention type</th>
          <th><span class="pill pill-sink">Sink</span></th>
          <th><span class="pill pill-local">Local</span></th>
          <th><span class="pill pill-retrieval">Retrieval</span></th>
          <th><span class="pill pill-induction">Induction</span></th>
          <th>Total</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>GPT-2 Medium</td><td>MHA</td><td>15</td><td>311</td><td>13</td><td>45</td><td>384</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Qwen-0.5B</td><td>GQA</td><td>9</td><td>288</td><td>3</td><td>36</td><td>336</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Qwen-1.5B</td><td>GQA</td><td>4</td><td>285</td><td>6</td><td>41</td><td>336</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Llama-3.2-1B</td><td>GQA</td><td>0</td><td>435</td><td>1</td><td>76</td><td>512</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="callout reveal">
    <strong>Why 81–86% Local?</strong> Local heads are the default state of the developmental
    manifold. Specialising into Retrieval or Induction requires sufficient training signal from
    tasks that reward long-range recall. Most heads never receive enough such signal to cross
    the bifurcation point.
  </div>
</div>
</Layout>
<style>
.section { max-width:820px; margin:0 auto; padding:3rem 2.5rem 8rem; }
.section h2 { font-size:clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.2rem); font-weight:200; letter-spacing:-.04em; line-height:1.15; margin-bottom:1.25rem; }
.section p { color:var(--text-2); font-weight:300; line-height:1.75; margin-bottom:1rem; }
</style>
